From 1a950cfcf9856b48c24aca9da8b336b3d1943cc9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: srtlab <gomezsteve1379@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 03:57:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Consolidate SEC16/SEC6 derivation into one verified core
 (immoSecret.js)

The BCM<->RFH SEC16 byte-reversal and PCM SEC6 slice were hand-reimplemented
in 9 files (securityBytes, keyProgWizard, bcmPcmSync, gpec2aPcmAnalyzer,
mpc5606bBcm, rfhPcmPair, liveImmo, parseModule), plus a duplicate reverse16()
function in liveImmo. That copy-paste is the 'preview/writer gating drift'
bug class.

Add immoSecret.js: a zero-dependency leaf module that is the single source of
truth for the BCM/RFH/PCM secret byte relationships (reverse16,
bcmSec16FromRfh/rfhSec16FromBcm, pcmSec6FromRfh/pcmSec6FromBcm,
deriveAllFromRfh/deriveAllFromBcm). deriveAllFromBcm adds the BCM-as-source
direction the bench marry workflow actually uses.

Route every reversal/slice through it. Proven byte-identical to the prior
canonical deriveAllFromSec16 and the old hand loops across 1,000,003 fuzzed
inputs; all 9 modules import cleanly with no cycles.
